\begin_layout Subsection
Sample space
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In probability theory, sample space captures the all possible values that
 a random trail can take on.
 The sample space is usually noted as sets of all possible outcomes.
 Sample space is often denoted by symbol Ωs.The sample space can be finite
 or infinite set.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Ordered sampling
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ordered sampling is a type of sampling in which the particular event after
 happening can happen again.
 For instance, for a 4 digit password, we can pick 1 of the 10 possible
 digits (1,2,...,9,0) then we have 10^4 possibilities.
\end_layout

